e transient, how new immigrants are challenging the claims of the old, and how that cycle is threatened as never before by the specter of gentrification.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCommunity development, UrbanxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aCommunity development, UrbanzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aEthnicityxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aEthnicityzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aGentrificationxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aGentrificationzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aSociology, UrbanxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aSociology, UrbanzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aUrban anthropologyxNew York (State)xNew York. 0aUrban anthropologyzNew York (State)zNew York. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aafrican americans.  aamerica.  aanthropologists.  aanthropology.  achinese americans.  aclass differences.  aeast harlem.  aethnic differences.  agender studies.  agentrification.  aharlem residents.  ahousing.  aimmigrant experiences.  ainner city life.  aitalian americans.  anew york.  anonfiction biography.  aoral histories.  apersonal stories.  apuerto ricans.  arace issues.  asociology.  astreet life.  atransient living.  aundocumented mexicans.  aunited states.  aurban history.  aurban life.  awest africa.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093954740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520939547423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520939547/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles